



Sir,
Philada Decr 8. 1775



This will be delivered to you by Mr Jonathan Smith a gentlemen of this city who with two others is charged with 500.000
[513]
dollars for the use of the army under your command.1 I have the honor to be Sir Your obedient humble Servt

John Hancock Presidt


I shall Dispatch an Express this Day to you by order of Congress in Consequence of your Letter of 28th ulto.

